      <p class="connection-callout__body">El Paso County's <strong>284 metro districts</strong> are chartered under Colorado law (<strong>CRS Title 32</strong>). The state's <a href="#scope-state">DOLA registry</a> holds parallel governance data; CDPHE holds mortality and environmental-health records on the same geography. When a district hides its own records, both the County Assessor (Local) and DOLA (State) are filing paths that work in parallel.</p>
